U.S.-based Juju musician Olu Fajemirokun aka ‘Olomori’ is set to bounce back on the scene with the release of a new album entitled ‘Laju E.’ In a recent chat, Fajemirokun said the new album is inspired by happenings around the world, especially in Nigeria. He also said the album will reawaken the lull in the Nigerian Juju music industry.   Depression notifies me when to switch my style – Rema     I’m inspired by Burna Boy’s tenancity – Blaqbonez     Yul Edochie calls out Ahmed Musa over post   Continuing, Fajemirokun said the album is a well-researched album that will shake the music industry like his hit album, ‘Olomori’. The album, Fajemirokun also said, will be marketed and distributed by Exotic Records owned by Olusegun Awofe Adegbesan. Adegbesan, in a recent chat, said the album will be widely circulated and it will touch all the nooks and crannies of Nigeria and be available electronically.